				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What Song in Groups (Level 51)?<a name="48594"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 27 04 2:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The bard is a jack of all trades.  You can fill the gaps left in your group.  If you do your job well your groupmates probably wont notice, but will be saying things like: &quot;...this is a good group...&quot; &quot;...I thought these mobs hit harder than this...&quot; &quot;...you guys wanna do a hard LDoN?..&quot;
<br />

<br />
If you have someone in your group hasting then your haste component probably won't stack, but the other stats from your song will.  Next level you get Battlecry.  This 'overhaste' does stack and will become a staple.
<br />

<br />
Similarly if you have a shammy slowing, don't bother with your slow for that effect.  The snare component may still be useful (know your slow percentage - I get asked sometimes when LFG).
<br />

<br />
When I was 51 I regularly used Katta's for the insane Dex.  Monks and Warriors love it.  I'd add this into your lineup if I were you (in downtime pulse it with drums and get your tank and DPS to tell you their Dex stat - good for a giggle).
<br />

<br />
If you're pet heavy, prolly mana song.
<br />

<br />
If you are fighting casters think about singing a resist song.  Bards are good for resists.  Guardian Rhythms or Psalm of Mystic Shielding for the MR, or a DS depending on what you are fighting.
<br />

<br />
Always have your Charm and Mez up.  If you are pulling, and need it, your trusty lvl 8 lull.  I'd leave that part of your lineup unchanged.
<br />

<br />
I'd drop SoS, use it in downtime for soaking up canni damage if you got a shammy.  Niv's would probably be better in combat.
<br />

<br />
Don't discount CoB - your level 1 song.  Chuck it in the mix till you need to replace it with something particular.  If you're light on healers, twist some health.
<br />

<br />
Your role will also change according to whether you're melee or instruments.
<br />

<br />
The best thing you can do is familiarise yourself with the songlist - which is a tough ask, it's getting pretty comprehensive at 51.  The secret is to be creative.  Know your class.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
