			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What Song in Groups (Level 51)?<a name="48825"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 28 04 5:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is a great time to be a bard because all of your tools work.  My twist during this time was (more or less)
<br />

<br />
1) amp
<br />
2) largos
<br />
3) VOV
<br />
4) Nivs
<br />
5) mana
<br />
6) guardian/purifing/elemental 
<br />
7) mez
<br />
8) charm
<br />

<br />
Dont underestimate the affects largos has.  It reduces ac and agi (which further reduces ac).  Mobs go down much faster even if your slow doesnt stack.  Also you can pre-slow which will save healers some mana.
<br />

<br />
You can also swap in damage sheilds (psalms) for some extra damage.  
<br />

<br />
I also prefered nivs and carnillian(sp - mana song) over cantana because mana is often more important that the difference in regen.
<br />

<br />
If you play with a regular group, charm can be an excellent tool for the next couple of levels.  However, it takes some time for people to get used to what you are doing and in pickup groups many players will get irritated at either wasting mana &amp; time on a charm mob or waiting for charm to break.
<br />

<br />
At this level it is often hard to visualize your contribution but Rubidium said it right people will notice that everything is easier.
<br />
 </span></td>
